        <detaileddescription>
<para>Tears down the running asio server (if any) and clears all registered tools. Use before unloading DLLs whose translation units called <computeroutput>addTool</computeroutput> — their captured std::function deleters dangle once those DLLs are unmapped, so a later <computeroutput>~Server</computeroutput> would segfault. Idempotent. Safe to call when nothing was registered. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
